label.value: mesonephric capsule specification

value.value: The regionalization process in which the identity of the mesonephric capsule is specified. Identity is considered to be the aggregate of characteristics by which a structure is recognized.

label.value: mesonephric renal vesicle induction

value.value: Signaling at short range between cells of the ureteric bud terminus and the kidney mesenchyme that positively regulates the formation of the mesonephric renal vesicle.

label.value: regulation of mesenchymal cell apoptotic process involved in mesonephric nephron morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the occurrence or rate of mesenchymal stem cell death by apoptotic process that contributes to the shaping of the nephron in the mesonephros.

label.value: negative regulation of mesenchymal cell apoptotic process involved in mesonephric nephron morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that reduces the occurrence or rate of mesenchymal stem cell death by apoptotic process that contributes to the shaping of the nephron in the mesonephros.

label.value: positive regulation of mesenchymal cell apoptotic process involved in mesonephric nephron morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that increases the occurrence or rate of mesenchymal stem cell death by apoptotic process that contributes to the shaping of the nephron in the mesonephros.

label.value: retina vasculature development in camera-type eye

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the vasculature of the retina over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label.value: retina vasculature morphogenesis in camera-type eye

value.value: The process in which the vasculature of the retina is generated and organized.

label.value: cerebellum vasculature development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the vasculature of the cerebellum over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label.value: cerebellum vasculature morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the vasculature of the cerebellum is generated and organized.

label.value: smooth muscle cell-matrix adhesion

value.value: The binding of a smooth muscle cell to the extracellular matrix via adhesion molecules.

label.value: cornea development in camera-type eye

value.value: The progression of the cornea over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The cornea is the transparent structure that covers the anterior of the eye.

label.value: retinal blood vessel morphogenesis

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a blood vessel of the retina over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label.value: maintenance of bipolar cell polarity regulating cell shape

value.value: The maintenance of established bipolar anisotropic intracellular organization or cell growth patterns that results in the shaping of a cell.

label.value: cardiac neural crest cell differentiation involved in heart development

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a cardiac neural crest cell that will migrate to the heart and contribute to its development. Cardiac neural crest cells are specialized cells that migrate toward the heart from the third, fourth and sixth pharyngeal arches.

label.value: cardiac neural crest cell development involved in heart development

value.value: The process aimed at the progression of a cardiac neural crest cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to its specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell that contributes to the development of the heart.

label.value: cardiac neural crest cell development involved in outflow tract morphogenesis

value.value: The process aimed at the progression of a cardiac neural crest cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to its specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell that contributes to the shaping of the outflow tract.

label.value: cell surface receptor signaling pathway involved in heart development

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by a ligand the binding to its receptor on the surface of a cell, which contributes to the progression of the heart over time.

label.value: fibroblast growth factor receptor signaling pathway involved in heart development

value.value: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a fibroblast growth factor receptor binding to one of its physiological ligands and contributing to the progression of the heart over time.

label.value: Notch signaling involved in heart development

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by binding of an extracellular ligand to a Notch receptor on the surface of the target cell and contributing to the progression of the heart over time.

label.value: canonical Wnt signaling pathway involved in heart development

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by binding of a Wnt protein to a frizzled family receptor on the surface of the target cell, followed by propagation of the signal via beta-catenin, and ending with a change in transcription of target genes that contributes to the progression of the heart over time. In this pathway, the activated receptor signals via downstream effectors that result in the inhibition of beta-catenin phosphorylation, thereby preventing degradation of beta-catenin. Stabilized beta-catenin can then accumulate and travel to the nucleus to trigger changes in transcription of target genes.

label.value: renal filtration cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features of a renal filtration cell. Renal filtration cells are specialized cells of the renal system that filter fluids by charge, size or both. Differentiation includes the processes involved in commitment of a cell to a specific fate and its subsequent development to the mature state.

label.value: nephrocyte differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized structural and/or functional features of a nephrocyte. A nephrocyte is an insect renal cell that filters hemolymph. Differentiation includes the processes involved in commitment of a cell to a specific fate and its subsequent development to the mature state.

label.value: pericardial nephrocyte differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized structural and/or functional features of a pericardial nephrocyte. A pericardial nephrocyte is an insect renal cell that filters hemolymph and is found with other pericardial nephrocytes in two rows flanking the dorsal vessel. Differentiation includes the processes involved in commitment of a cell to a specific fate and its subsequent development to the mature state.

label.value: garland nephrocyte differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized structural and/or functional features of a garland nephrocyte. A garland nephrocyte is an insect renal cell that filters hemolymph and forms a ring with other garland nephrocytes around the esophagus. Differentiation includes the processes involved in commitment of a cell to a specific fate and its subsequent development to the mature state.

label.value: disseminated nephrocyte differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized structural and/or functional features of a disseminated nephrocyte. A disseminated nephrocyte is an insect renal cell that filters hemolymph and is found at scattered locations in the fat body or other tissues. Differentiation includes the processes involved in commitment of a cell to a specific fate and its subsequent development to the mature state.

label.value: cell proliferation involved in heart morphogenesis

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the shaping of the heart.

label.value: cell proliferation involved in outflow tract morphogenesis

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the shaping of the outflow tract.

label.value: renal tubule development

value.value: The progression of the renal tubule over time from its formation to the mature form. A renal tubule is a tube that filters, re-absorbs and secretes substances to rid an organism of waste and to play a role in fluid homeostasis.

label.value: anterior Malpighian tubule development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the anterior Malpighian tubule over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The pair of anterior tubules arise from a dorsal region of the embryonic hindgut and projects forwards through the body cavity. A Malpighian tubule is a fine, thin-walled excretory tubule in insects which connects with the posterior part of the gut.

label.value: posterior Malpighian tubule development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the posterior Malpighian tubule over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The pair of posterior tubules arise from a ventrolateral region of the embryonic hindgut and project backwards through the body cavity. A Malpighian tubule is a fine, thin-walled excretory tubule in insects which connects with the posterior part of the gut.

label.value: Malpighian tubule principal cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a Malpighian tubule principal cell. A Malpighian tubule principal cell is an epithelial secretory cell that transports cations into the lumen of the tubule.

label.value: Malpighian tubule stellate cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a Malpighian tubule stellate cell. A Malpighian tubule stellate cell is a specialized epithelial secretory cell that moves chloride ions and water across the tubule epithelium.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in Malpighian tubule morphogenesis

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population and contributing to the shaping of a Malpighian tubule.

label.value: Malpighian tubule bud morphogenesis

value.value: The morphogenetic process in which a bud forms from the embryonic hindgut tube to form the Malpighian tubule. A bud is a protrusion that forms from the tube by localized changes in cell shape and position.

label.value: renal tubule morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the renal tubule is generated by specification of cell fate, through the maintenance of cell polarity, regulated cell proliferation and morphogenetic cell rearrangements, shape changes and growth. A renal tubule is a tube that filters, re-absorbs and secretes substances to rid an organism of waste and to play a role in fluid homeostasis.

label.value: cell rearrangement involved in Malpighian tubule morphogenesis

value.value: The movement of an epithelial cell with respect to other epithelial cells that contributes to the shaping of the Malpighian tubule.

label.value: cell growth involved in Malpighian tubule morphogenesis

value.value: The growth of an epithelial cell dependent on cycles of endoreplication, where growth contributes to the shaping of the Malpighian tubule.

label.value: cell morphogenesis involved in Malpighian tubule morphogenesis

value.value: The shape change of an epithelial cell from a columnar to squamous cell morphology that contributes to the shaping of the Malpighian tubule.

label.value: cardiac conduction

value.value: Transfer of an organized electrical impulse across the heart to coordinate the contraction of cardiac muscles. The process begins with generation of an action potential (in the sinoatrial node (SA) in humans) and ends with a change in the rate, frequency, or extent of the contraction of the heart muscles.

label.value: establishment or maintenance of monopolar cell polarity

value.value: Any cellular process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of monopolar intracellular organization or cell growth patterns. Monopolar cell organization is directional organization along an axis.

label.value: establishment or maintenance of monopolar cell polarity regulating cell shape

value.value: Any cellular process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of a monopolar intracellular organization or cell growth patterns that regulate the shape of a cell.

label.value: non-canonical Wnt signaling pathway involved in heart development

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by binding of a Wnt protein to a frizzled family receptor on the surface of the target cell, followed by propagation of the signal via effectors other than beta-catenin and contributing to the progression of the heart over time.

label.value: cell adhesion involved in heart morphogenesis

value.value: The attachment of a cell, either to another cell or to an underlying substrate such as the extracellular matrix, via cell adhesion molecules that contributes to the shaping of the heart.

label.value: regulation of cell adhesion involved in heart morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that modulates the extent of cell adhesion contributing to the shaping of the heart.

label.value: planar cell polarity pathway involved in cardiac muscle cell fate commitment

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by binding of a Wnt protein to a frizzled family receptor on the surface of the target cell, followed by propagation of the signal via effectors other than beta-catenin and contributing to a cardioblast being committed to a cardiac muscle cell fate.

label.value: neural precursor cell proliferation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of neural precursor cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population. A neural precursor cell is either a nervous system stem cell or a nervous system progenitor cell.

label.value: cell chemotaxis involved in Malpighian tubule morphogenesis

value.value: The directed movement of the outgrowing Malpighian tubule guided by specific chemical cues/signals. Movement may be towards a guidance cue (positive chemotaxis) or away from it (negative chemotaxis). Guidance contributes to the final positioning of the tubule.

label.value: Wnt protein secretion

value.value: The controlled release of a Wnt protein from a cell.

label.value: regulation of Wnt protein secretion

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of a Wnt protein from a cell.

label.value: positive regulation of Wnt protein secretion

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of a Wnt protein from a cell.
